 "awd_abstract_narration": "EEC-0084731\r\nDrake\r\n\r\nThis Study will address the effects that extended cold storage conditions such as those encountered in extended shelf life refrigerated foods (cold stress, cold/acid stress) have on subsequent growth characteristics, heat tolerance, acid tolerance, freeze thaw stability, and virulence factor expression of E. coli O157:H7.  Studies will be conducted in broth as well as in a model food system, skim milk.  A better understanding of the effects of cold storage and cold/acid storage on subsequent growth characteristics and virulence of E. coli O157:H7 will enable design of food processing and storage regimes to minimize risk and will expand knowledge of cold adaptation of this foodborne pathogen.\r\n",
